The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 6: Sun Pharmaceutical has accused the board of Taro Pharmaceutical of trying to sidestep real issues as the two companies continue to lock horns over their failed merger deal. Taro Pharmaceutical rejected Suns proposal to increase the offer price to bring an end to their dispute, and it called for a shareholders referendum.                             
	 Calcutta, Jan. 6: The United Bank of India will reduce PLR by 50 basis points to 13 per cent from January 12. The bank said it would pass on the benefit to all existing and new borrowers. The deposit rates will also be realigned, it said.                             
	 New Delhi, Jan. 6: A penalty of Rs 133.23 crore along with a fine of Rs 200 per day has been imposed on British Airways as the airline has not paid service tax on the tickets sold in 2006-07 but collected the tax from the passengers.                             
	 Mumbai, Jan. 6: Vodafone and Research In Motion (RIM) has launched the BlackBerry Pearl Flip smartphone in India, priced at Rs 21,999. The BlackBerry Pearl Flip 8220 smartphone has a 2 megapixel camera with digital zoom.                             
	 Calcutta, Jan. 6: BOC India, a member of the Linde group, has signed a 15-year long term contract with Rourkela Steel Plant for supply of gas.                                                                                                                           
